social_posts.post_text:
And we’re back! Happy new year everyone!
SDCC 2022 reminded me how much I love cosplay, but simultaneously gave me a new perspective. I’m not anywhere near as focused on social media as I used to be, which has been really good for me. I used to just share what photos I did have and didn’t intentionally make content for IG, and I’m going to go back to that. So while my posting will be sparse, hopefully the quality will be improved. 
I can’t wait for some projects I have coming up this spring and SDCC2023! If I can pull it off, I think I may be doing my most ambitious cosplay yet. 
#ravencosplay #sdcc #cosplay

I’m so happy I got to be a part of this group and cosplay again! Since COVID hit, my motivation for cosplay went way down since a lot of it is social for me. This shoot was such a creative breath of fresh air 🥰✨ 
(Also big shout out to my parents for letting us use their backyard for our weeb adventures lol)
